  <abstract>This Honorable Discharge document for Spencer S. Ferguson is dated 8 Feb., 1919. It contains a physical description of him and is signed by Major Joseph Wilkinson at Camp Sheridan, Ala. This discharge was issued for the convenience of the army in accordance with Circular 106, W[ar] D[epartment]. Also includes Ferguson's enlistment record as private first class at Hickman County, Tenn. On April 27, 1918. Apparently he re-enlisted in Dec. 1919 at Fort Oglethorpe, Ga.</abstract>
